OL,3,CLib Dems celebrate taking Portsmouth
OL,4,Cas Labour loses control of Southampton
OL,6,FThe Liberal Democrats have celebrated
OL,7,Ftaking control of Portsmouth City
OL,8,FCouncil in this year's local
OL,9,Felections, with the party's leader,
OL,10,FSir Ed Davey, telling his rivals to
OL,11,F"smell the coffee".
OL,13,FSir Ed told ITV Meridian that the Lib
OL,14,FDems' results show that the "old
OL,15,Fparties are out" - referencing the
OL,16,FConservatives and Labour.
OL,18,FThe development is one of a number of
OL,19,Fcrucial results in Hampshire, with
OL,20,Fchanges across the political divide.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
