PN,41303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1778242270
OL,3,CLib Dems celebrate taking Portsmouth
OL,4,Cas Labour loses control of Southampton
OL,6,FLabour remains the largest party on
OL,7,Fthe council with 24 seats, but is two
OL,8,Fshort of a majority, while Reform has
OL,9,Feight, the Liberal Democrats have
OL,10,Fseven, and the Conservatives and
OL,11,FGreens both have six.
OL,13,FSir Ed celebrated his party's win in
OL,14,FPortsmouth by handing out cups of
OL,15,Fcoffee to jubilant supporters.
OL,17,FThe Lib Dems kept every one of their
OL,18,Fseats which they were defending and
OL,19,Fand made gains of three.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
